<DOC><DOCNO> DOE2-09-0597 </DOCNO><TEXT>The paper describes a project in progress in the UK Department of Energy'sEconomics and Statistics Division. A fourth generation language/database,Focus, is being used to construct a fuel and energy database. The systemis designed to store regular statistics from fuel industries, time seriesdata, and the results of statistical analysis, modelling and forecasting.Data and process catalogues index the subjects of statistics, sourcedocuments, statistical procedures, and publication of data. Retrieveddata can be presented in the formats used by several software packages,to encourage the use of packages for routine production of statisticsand, where appropriate, for analysis and forecasting.</TEXT></DOC>